Marvell Falls After Sales Forecast Trails Analysts’ Estimates

-- B y   I a n   K i n g
-- 
2011-03-03T23:30:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/marvell-falls-after-sales-forecast-trails-analysts-estimates.html
  Marvell Technology Group Ltd. (MRVL) , the
maker of processors for the BlackBerry phone, declined as much
as 7.8 percent in extended trading after predicting sales for
the first quarter that fell short of analysts’ estimates.  Revenue in the current period will be $800 million to $850
million, said Clyde Hosein, the  Santa Clara , California-based
company’s chief financial officer, on a conference call. That
compares with an average estimate of $882.5 million, according
to a Bloomberg survey of 21 analysts.  Shares fell as much as $1.42 to $16.80. The stock rose 23
cents, or 1.3 percent, to $18.22 at 4 p.m. New York time in
regular Nasdaq Stock Market trading.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian King in  San Francisco  at 
 ianking@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tom Giles at   tgiles5@bloomberg.net  